  "timeframe": "1D",
  "market_context": "After a smart money reversal (change in state of delivery and market structure shift), price retested an old bearish fair value gap (SIBI) from the prior sell side of the curve, using it as support to move higher toward buyside liquidity.",
  "key_observation": "An old bearish fair value gap (SIBI) formed during the prior downtrend was retested after the reversal and acted as support for a higher move to sweep buyside liquidity at 1984.0.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identify equal highs above current price and mark the Cy (candle 2 closure) level as a potential reversal trigger.",
    "Step 2: Confirm smart money reversal via close over the Cy and close over preceding down-close candles, establishing a new bullish bias.",
    "Step 3: Locate old fair value gaps on the prior sell side of the curve (bearish SIBI) that could serve as reaccumulation zones.",
    "Step 4: Observe price retesting and closing above the old bearish FVG (1912–1924 zone), then using it as support to rally higher.",
    "Step 5: Anticipate and confirm sweep of buyside liquidity at 1984.0 following the reaccumulation off the old FVG."
  ],
  "outcome": "Price rallied from the old FVG zone (1912–1924) to sweep buyside liquidity at 1984.0, confirming the reaccumulation setup.",
  "lessons": "Old fair value gaps from the opposite side of the market maker curve can be powerful reaccumulation zones after a confirmed smart money reversal; they provide high-probability support when price returns to them.",
